Plot.
While digging an extension in the London underground, workers come across
skeletal remains. Construction is halted and paleontologist Dr. Matthew
Roney's team take over. They soon find a metal object that they initially
think might be a bomb but turns out to be an alien spacecraft of some kind.
Roney's assistant Barbara Judd and Professor Bernard Quatermass, a rocket
specialist who does experimental work for the Ministry of Defence, discover
that much of the housing around the site was abandoned by its inhabitants
40 years ago because of strange noises and what was believed to be ghosts.
Inside the spacecraft they find the remnants of insect-like creatures, all
now dead. In disturbing the craft however, they release an invisible force
of immense power.
